{"ts":"2026-07-13T09:17:31.743Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-hno5"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-542: MCP pm_copy nests title/message under options while sibling tools declare flat camelCase params — own suite triggers unexpected-arg warnings"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":""},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","contracts","gh-issue","mcp"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-13T09:17:31.743Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-13T09:17:31.743Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":90},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm_copy inputSchema declares title/message (and idOnly if supported) as flat top-level params derived from COPY_FLAG_CONTRACTS; options stays accepted for back-compat; Contract test asserts every narrow tool's declared top-level keys cover its action's flag contract (options-vs-flat drift fails fast); MCP integration suites run warning-clean: pm_close 'text' arg fixed and zero unexpected-top-level-argument warnings asserted"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-mpbb"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"cc0c752ffa24d4c304f2dda47e69c33dabe8f13befb3e7af0e43a3f68e8cdced","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-07-13T09:17:45.083Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"The MCP boundary's declared-keys warning (shipped by pm-qxwu via pm-at83) is only trustworthy if each tool's declared surface matches what the runtime actually accepts. pm_copy under-declares: runtime handler spreads args into runAction so flat title/message work, but the schema routes them through nested options — the ONLY narrow mutation tool shaped this way. Evidence in-repo: tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts ~:1340 passes flat title/message/idOnly and every CI run emits 3 warnings; same suite passes 'text' to pm_close (not a real param, silently ignored — assertion value untested). Class framing: this is the INPUT-side sibling of pm-srns (uniform output contract) and belongs to the mpbb declared-contract-rendering ledger family (6y58/9qcr/ulqu render FROM contract domain; this one DECLARES from contract). Fix in tool-definitions.ts by deriving from COPY_FLAG_CONTRACTS, not by hand-adding keys."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-13T09:17:45.083Z"}],"before_hash":"cc0c752ffa24d4c304f2dda47e69c33dabe8f13befb3e7af0e43a3f68e8cdced","after_hash":"7f001ebbca31c7a57a3cc77dc5cd3de0ea2dc0b586bff22f9702af2fef951766"}
{"ts":"2026-07-13T09:17:55.552Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"note_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-13T09:17:55.552Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-13T09:17:55.552Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Scope extension (pass #77, 2026-07-13): the fenced ignore block MUST also cover .agents/pm/locks/ — concrete failure: review pass #76's commit (67ccbcf4) accidentally committed .agents/pm/locks/reindex.lock (a live-pid runtime lock) because this repo's .gitignore covered runtime/ and search/ but not locks/. The tracked-cache health warning (AC half 3) should likewise flag tracked lock files. Our own repo's .gitignore gets the locks/ line directly this pass; pm init's fenced block owns it for user repos."}]}],"before_hash":"7f001ebbca31c7a57a3cc77dc5cd3de0ea2dc0b586bff22f9702af2fef951766","after_hash":"7f26e86c9e9cdd34a2e5dc8dd6443d73bb0aa807fd72f224cdf90401f8d47bf5"}
